&lt;p&gt;General Atlantic is looking to hire a Workday Integration Lead in our New York Office. The Integration Lead for Workday Finance, HCM and Payroll is responsible for designing, implementing, and managing integrations between Workday modules and other systems, as well as support and enhance our Extend applications. This role requires technical expertise in Workday&#39;s integration capabilities, financial processes, payroll management, and HCM, as well as strong functional knowledge of the same subject areas, to support thoughtful, sustainable implementations and smooth ongoing operations. This position plays a critical role in ensuring cross-system data integrity and enabling clean data flow between Workday and third-party applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our current Workday footprint includes Workday’s core HCM &amp;amp; Finance modules, PRISM and Extend. &amp;nbsp;The role requires active collaboration with end user stakeholders in our Human Capital and Finance teams, as well as within IT with our Product Management, Data Engineering, Infrastructure/Security and interfacing application teams.&lt;/p&gt;
